      Utility: The aadhaar card became even more important, and SEBI released an e-KYC list, check the details!

      By Newscrab Jr Editor | Thu, 9 Feb 2023

      The importance of the Aadhaar card has been enhanced by the Security and Exchange Board of India (SEBI). The market regulator has released a list of 30 institutions that can use the unique ID number for e-KYC. These institutions are related to financial services. Now, these entities can use the Aadhaar Authentication Service for various purposes. The decision comes two years after listing eight agencies that can use UIDAI's Aadhaar authentication service.

      These 39 companies include Bang Securities, NJ India Invest, and Muthoot Securities. Agencies on the list include IndusInd Banking Services, Orbis Financial Corporation, Indo-Money Securities, HSB Securities & Equities, Flourish Fincap, and Vogue Commercial Companies.

      SEBI said in a circular that listing these companies would curb money laundering. All these companies will first tie-up with KU. Then they have to register themselves with UIDAI as Sub-KU. UIDAI will frame the agreement. After this, these companies will be onboarded as per the rules.

      This means that for any market-related activities, a person will need to have an Aadhaar card. Since these companies can now do KYC using an Aadhaar card, it will be much easier to get KYC done as compared to other means.

      Aadhaar card is already very important for almost all economic activities. The UIDAI project has now simplified the process of obtaining a SIM card, banking, and other selling and buying activities.

      Meanwhile, the Income Tax Department has warned that those who do not get their PAN card linked with an Aadhaar card may have to pay a fine. His PAN card will also be canceled. The last date for Aadhaar-PAN linking is December 31.
